social_posts.post_text: thank you all so much for a fantastic year! truly so grateful to be creating and sharing music that excites me and represents all the parts of me to the fullest. Welcome to part 1 of the 12 Days Of Demos! This month I am leaking parts to 12 new songs you’ve never heard and ones I’m really excited about!! 

This one is called “Heavy” and it is my favorite song I’ve ever written 🥹 I wrote it the day I came out of the closet to my family bc it was a really big decision for me and a very scary conversation that had weighed on my mind and heart for a long time. I honestly never thought I’d tell them but writing this song freed me of the pressure I was putting on myself to be someone else. I’m really hopeful that this song will bring comfort to anyone who feels like the weight of the world is on their shoulders. I’m with you and you aren’t alone. When you are ready, we can cut that leash and be clouds together ☁️ 

#wlw #bi #gay #queerartist #lgbtqia #music #newmusic #originalsong

Welcome to part 4 of the 12 Days Of Demo’s! This month I am leaking parts to 12 new songs you’ve never heard and ones I’m really excited about!! 

This one is called “Carolina Girl”. I wrote this song for my parents. I moved to Nashville from South Carolina when I was 16 years old to pursue music. My family has been so supportive my entire life and I have times where I’ve been insecure that I didn’t grow up to be exactly who my parents thought I’d be. I have a different idea of what my life should look like and that is ok because I know what is best for me. But with this song, I wanted to remind them that no matter where I go, what I do or who I become, I will always be their carolina girl. 

#originialsong #demo #southcarolina #songwriting

Welcome to part 5 of the 12 Days Of Demo’s! This month I am leaking parts to 12 new songs you’ve never heard and ones I’m really excited about!! 

This one is called “Valley Girl” and I wrote it for anyone who has been left out of the blue or cheated on. I had a situationship where the guy I was seeing told me that on and on that he wanted the bachelor, night life and didn’t want to settle down. Then come to find he found someone else and got ENGAGED within a month. I wanted a to write a song to make me feel like the bad b!tch that I am and to remind me that no matter who someone leaves you for, it never makes you less. 

For those of you who don’t live in LA, “the Valley” is the suburban area of the city. They valley girl I am referencing is not a comment on the girl but on the type of lifestyle he said he never wanted but he is a damn liar. for christmas I’d like to give a big middle finger in the sky to that dude! 

#originialsong #breakup #cheating

Welcome to part 6 of the 12 Days Of Demo’s! This month I am leaking parts to 12 new songs you’ve never heard and ones I’m really excited about!! 

this is “songs about boys” a song that had a few different versions but this one really came together to say something i think we all have felt before. i went thru a break up that made me never want to listen to music again. it fucked me up beyond measure because I didn’t know where to take my pain, if not to music. when we wrote this song it channeled that part of my heart and made me feel seen. so when I sing “fuck you it’s all your fault that I can’t enjoy any songs about boys” know I am singing that with my entire chest. i hope you know who you are and you aren’t ruining music for another girl somewhere.

i was born in 1996 which everyone pretty much agrees is the cusp year between millenials and gen z. i never really understood why i didn’t fit into one box bc I grew up listening to britney spears, wearing a fake headset mic and a crop top around the house pretending to be a popstar but then i also grew up with technology and social media advancing faster than I could keep up with. so now i like listening to artists like tate mcrae and olivia rodrigo. 

i then moved to nashville to be a songwriter at 13 and taylor swift was the biggest inspo for everyone my age. so storytelling in my songs became super important to me. 

fast forward a few years later and I am a professional songwriter in the music industry with number one albums for kpop artists Red Velvet, ITZY, Class:y, Sorn, JoYuri (IZ*one) and ChoiYooJung (WekiMeki). so of course, kpop is a huge influence on my style of music, fashion and performance. 

I am a big blend of a lot of things because of my journey in the music industry. all i know is that if you like any of the artists mentioned above, you should check out my original music. the song you are listening to is called Romeo, out now! 

#britneyarmy #swifties #oliviarodrigo #tatemcrae #midzy #redvelvet #kpop #popmusic #millenial #genz

Welcome to part 11 of the 12 Days Of Demo’s! This month I am leaking parts to 12 new songs you’ve never heard and ones I’m really excited about!! 

this one is called “we built this house” and this song makes me CRYYYYYYY happy tears bc i wrote this song about the summer i moved in with my bf. we moved in together at the top of 2020 and really got to build our own little world. it was really special and i’m so grateful we could spend all of that time making our house a home. i am a huge fleetwood mac fan and i have always wanted to have a song that felt like it could have been on the rumors album (truly shooting for the stars here) and some organic harry styles influences. but i think it captures all of the emotions and passion i feel about my partner. we really built our house on love and for that reason, i never want to leave it.

2022 was such a magical year full of life and adventure. i put on my vision board that i wanted to tour in 2022 but the universe has a sense of humor bc i actually ended up traveling to 4 continents this year and 7 new countries. i got to experience so many walks of life and learned more about myself in one year than i have in a lifetime. 

a few highlights from this year were swimming with sea lions in the galapagos islands, traveling to europe with one of my best friends and writing a bunch of kpop songs in seoul, south korea. i wrote so much music and got to perform all over. when i was a kid, a big reason i decided to pursue music full time was because i wanted a job that would help me see the world. 

for 2023 i am setting the intention for myself that the music i make will be heard my millions. i am alive again releasing music and i’m going to be putting a ton of new songs out that i think really capture me and my experiences. sooooooo i can’t wait for you to hear!!!

i am so grateful to have all of the memories 2022 has brought me. truly one of the best years of my life. all i’ve ever wanted to do was something special and to quote the tattoo on my lower right arm “and so she did”.

elli 🌟

I wrote 'Moonshine' as a reminder that love is worth fighting for, even when it has to be kept in the shadows. The lyric 'we'll stand in the sun in due time, but for now we'll just lay right here in the moonshine' represents the hope that one day we can be together in the light, but for now, we'll find comfort and solace in each other's arms, even if it has to be in secret. It's a song about learning to accept that you may not be where you want to be yet, but you will be someday. It’s my love letter specifically to my lgbtq+ family 👩‍❤️‍💋‍👩 we are meant to shine, and though everyone may not understand, we know our time in the sun is just around the corner. i love you 🫶🏻

pov: you wrote this song to help anyone who might be in a closeted relationship with someone they love but they don’t feel safe to come out to their friends, family or the world. you are safe here, i love you and you are seen 🫶🏻👩‍❤️‍💋‍👩

This video used to bring me a lot of sadness. It was a very humiliating experience for a 17 year old girl who was just trying to figure out her place not only in the music industry but in the world. I took a huge break from music after this, and I started hanging out with @lyremusicgroup . She and I started making music together that I had no idea would lead to us writing THE songs that made my dreams of working in the music industry a reality. The point is, I didn’t know it then, but something that used to bring me so much pain was the catalyst to prove anyone who didn’t think I had what it took to make it wrong. So I hope this is inspiring to anyone pushing through the mud. No one can stop you but yourself. Keep going <3

I’m so lucky and kicking my feet bc I get to be playing more shows and releasing new music next year!!!! merry christmas from me and my corndog :)
i like to call this time of the year my annual sleep marathon 💋

january - shot the music video for my song ‘Green Juice’ and danced my lil tush off

february - played my first show in LA in a very long time and it was with my band boys who i love so much

march - flew to work in one of the most beautiful studios in the bahamas with one of my besties 

april - shot the cover of my ep ‘Drink Me’ and froze my tits off in the process

may- met the boys of nct dream with tish and this video is very important to me bc they were my top artist on my spotify wrapped 

june - it was a really big goal for me to start playing more shows this year so here is me playing another acoustic show

july- shot the music video for my song ‘crybaby’ and it is to date the most beautiful i have ever felt

august - spoke on a panel at kcon with my girls and got to meet kep1er which was cool bc I co-wrote their song ‘Giddy’

september - the first show on my very first ever tour as an opener (big deal)

october - still on tour (bigger deal)

november - got to hang with the girlies of blackswan and talk about music all night, really fun to get to know them!

december - last show of the year where I announced that next year i am opening in EUROPE for emlyn which i’m still processing how my life is even real

I was editing this together and having a very hard time picking which videos to feature because there were so many great moments. i can truly say this was one of the best years of my life!!!! i traveled all over to explore new places, play my music and meet some really cool people. I am very grateful and lucky beyond belief. truly stoked to see what 2024 has for me 🤍 i love you all sooooooooo much!!
